title: Georgia mom, boyfriend charged in toddler's death - Atlanta Journal Constitution
text: Georgia mom, boyfriend charged in toddler’s death Georgia mom, boyfriend charged in toddler’s death James Paul Cutshall (left), Marley Rena Wilson (Credit: Florida Times-Union) Story Highlights The 16-month-old girl suffered blunt-force trauma, according to a report. The mother and her boyfriend have been charged with felony murder. A South Georgia couple have been charged with felony murder after the woman’s 16-month-old daughter died, the Florida Times-Union reported. On Feb. 12, deputies and medical technicians in Brantley County responded to a child in respiratory distress, according to the report. The mother, Marley Rena Wilson, 18, said she put the child down with a bottle of milk and five minutes later “they heard her having problems breathing,” according to the incident report from the Brantley County Sheriff’s Office. Wilson also said she and her boyfriend, James Paul Cutshall, 19, performed CPR on the girl, according to the report. The child later died at a hospital in Waycross. A GBI autopsy showed that blunt-force trauma contributed to the child’s death, the newspaper reported. The couple have been arrested and remain in the Brantley County jail.
